The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the historic Adriatic Charter Summit in Montenegro, expressing the US' commitment to the Western Balkans. He highlighted the importance of the Adriatic Charter in bringing the countries of the Western Balkans closer to Europe and NATO. Pence also praised Montenegro's recent accession to NATO and encouraged other countries in the region to pursue their European future. He emphasized the need for unity in the face of threats such as terrorism and aggression from Russia, and called on all countries to fulfill their commitment to defense spending. Pence concluded by expressing his confidence in a bright future for the Western Balkans and the West as a whole.